    <h2 id="womens-microbiome">Why Women Need Strain-Specific Probiotics</h2>

    <p>The women's microbiome extends beyond the gut. The vaginal microbiome — dominated by Lactobacillus species in healthy women — maintains an acidic environment (pH 3.8-4.5) that serves as the primary defense against pathogenic bacteria, yeast overgrowth, and urinary tract infections. When this Lactobacillus dominance is disrupted (by antibiotics, hormonal changes, sexual activity, or stress), the vaginal pH rises, creating conditions favorable for bacterial vaginosis (BV), yeast infections, and UTIs.</p>

