    </div>

    <p>The gut-vaginal axis — the bidirectional communication pathway between intestinal and vaginal microbiomes — explains why oral probiotics can influence vaginal flora. Specific strains, particularly <em>L. rhamnosus</em> GR-1 and <em>L. reuteri</em> RC-14, have been shown in multiple clinical trials to migrate from the intestinal tract to the vaginal mucosa, restoring Lactobacillus dominance and acidic pH within 28 days of daily oral supplementation.</p>

